Second Attempt
--------------

8.6 lb red/green cabbage (73%)
3.2 lb fennel bulbs (27%)

((8.6 + 3.2) * 453.592) * 0.015 = 80.3
80.3 grams himalayan pink salt

[ per 10 lb ]
1 Tbsp juniper berries
2 Tbsp caraway seeds
2 tsp aniseed
2 tsp celery seeds
^ quick grind with fully ground salt

Finely slice cabbage/fennel
Mix and layer with salt/seasoning
Wait 30+ minutes (good time to clean)
Punch 'n mash
Ensure it'll be submerged below brine
Wait 3+ weeks (active CO2 for the first 3-5 days)

Results
+++++++

Tasty, but also kinda weak.
